House of Representatives Member representing Sumaila/Takai Federal constituency of Kano state, Hon. Shamsudeen Dambazau has said that the return of Alhaji Alhassan Doguwa, to the House of Representatives following his resounding victory at the Tudun Wada Doguwa Federal Constituency will enrich the green chamber considering his wealth of experience in the legislative business over the years. Hon. Dambazau further stated that Hon. Doguwa’s return was an indicative of his people’s implicit trust in his ability not only to bring quality representation but to ensure that that the the APC’s Next Level agenda was firmly rooted. Alhassan Doguwa of the APC scored 66,667 votes to defeat his closest rival, Alhaji Yushau Mohammed of the PDP who got 6,322 votes. In a congratulatory statement in honour of Hon Doguwa, Hon. Dambazau admonished that the he be magnanimous in victory and continue to deliver the dividends of democracy to his constituents. “In the last rerun election, the people of Kano State, most especially the people of Tudun Wada Doguwa Federal Constituency, demonstrated unequivocally their implicit trust and confidence in Hon Doguwa, thereby renewing the mandate of our party, the APC. “Let me assure the people that the Honourable Member would not take this sacred trust for granted but will ensure that the constituency and indeed the nation is taken to the next level through quality representation. “I am confident that my brother will justify the overwhelming reelection mandate bestowed him by the good people of his constituency, by redoubling its efforts in harnessing the potentials of his office and bringing people-focused development to Kano state and Nigeria as a whole.” The statement said.